strength=&#8221;0.3&#8243; width=&#8221;9\/12&#8243; tablet_width_inherit=&#8221;default&#8221; animation_type=&#8221;default&#8221; bg_image_animation=&#8221;none&#8221; border_type=&#8221;simple&#8221; column_border_width=&#8221;none&#8221; column_border_style=&#8221;solid&#8221;][divider line_type=&#8221;No Line&#8221; custom_height=&#8221;10&#8243;][toggles style=&#8221;minimal_small&#8221;][toggle color=&#8221;Extra-Color-1&#8243; heading_tag=&#8221;default&#8221; heading_tag_functionality=&#8221;default&#8221; title=&#8221;What is ANZSCO?&#8221;][vc_column_text css=&#8221;&#8221; text_direction=&#8221;default&#8221;]<span id=\"what-is-anzsco\">The <strong>Australian and New Zealand Standard Classification of Occupations<\/strong> (ANZSCO) is a skill-based classification system used to classify occupations in the Australian and New Zealand labour markets.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>ANZSCO was maintained by the Australian Bureau of Statistics (<a class=\"uline\" href=\"https:\/\/www.abs.gov.au\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">ABS<\/a> <i class=\"icon-tiny fa fa-external-link\"><\/i>) and consists of a list of occupations, each of which is assigned a unique 6-digit code. The last revision, ANZSCO v.2022, was released on 22 November 2022, and no further updates will be made.<\/p>\n<p>Despite the introduction of a new classification system (OSCA), <strong>ANZSCO is still used by the Department of Home Affairs for skilled visa programs<\/strong>. This means ANZSCO remains the <strong>official framework for assessing an applicant\u2019s skills against a nominated occupation in Australia<\/strong> until OSCA is fully implemented in the migration system.[\/vc_column_text][vc_column_text][\/vc_column_text][\/toggle][toggle color=&#8221;Extra-Color-1&#8243; heading_tag=&#8221;default&#8221; heading_tag_functionality=&#8221;default&#8221; title=&#8221;What is OSCA? When will it replace ANZSCO?&#8221;][vc_column_text css=&#8221;&#8221; text_direction=&#8221;default&#8221;]<span id=\"what-is-anzsco\">The <strong>Occupation Standard Classification for Australia<\/strong> (<a class=\"uline\" href=\"https:\/\/www.abs.gov.au\/statistics\/classifications\/osca-occupation-standard-classification-australia\/2024-version-1-0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">OSCA<\/a> <i class=\"icon-tiny fa fa-external-link\"><\/i>)<strong> version 1.0<\/strong> was officially released on 6 December 2024 as Australia\u2019s new national occupation classification system.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>OSCA is designed to better reflect Australia\u2019s evolving labour market by providing more updated occupation classifications than ANZSCO. However, <strong>OSCA has not yet been adopted by the Department of Home Affairs for visa and migration purposes<\/strong>.[\/vc_column_text][vc_column_text][\/vc_column_text][\/toggle][toggle color=&#8221;Extra-Color-1&#8243; heading_tag=&#8221;default&#8221; heading_tag_functionality=&#8221;default&#8221; title=&#8221;What is Anzscosearch?&#8221;][vc_column_text css=&#8221;&#8221; text_direction=&#8221;default&#8221;]<span id=\"what-is-anzscosearch\">Anzscosearch is a comprehensive search tool designed to help users navigate Australia\u2019s skilled migration system. It is built on the ANZSCO catalogue and integrates all Federal and State\/Territory skilled occupation lists in one platform.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>With Anzscosearch, users can quickly find information on:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>General Skilled Migration (GSM) visa options<\/li>\n<li>Occupation eligibility under various skilled migration programs<\/li>\n<li>State and Territory nomination availability<\/li>\n<li>and more (see our <a class=\"uline\" href=\"https:\/\/www.anzscosearch.com\/subscription\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Features<\/a>)<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>Anzscosearch is\u00a0<strong>daily reviewed<\/strong> and updated (if necessary) to ensure accuracy and up-to-date occupation listings. Whether you\u2019re searching for visa pathways, occupation classifications, or state nomination details, Anzscosearch simplifies the process by providing all relevant information in one place.[\/vc_column_text][vc_column_text][\/vc_column_text][\/toggle][toggle color=&#8221;Extra-Color-1&#8243; heading_tag=&#8221;default&#8221; heading_tag_functionality=&#8221;default&#8221; title=&#8221;What does the Anzscosearch tool provide?&#8221;][vc_column_text]Anzscosearch provides up-to-date information about General skilled migration visas for Australia and information about all Australian State\/Territory skilled occupation lists.<\/p>\n<p>It also provides 6 types of search.[\/vc_column_text][divider line_type=&#8221;No Line&#8221; custom_height=&#8221;20&#8243;][vc_row_inner equal_height=&#8221;yes&#8221; column_margin=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction_tablet=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction_phone=&#8221;default&#8221; left_padding_desktop=&#8221;20&#8243; constrain_group_2=&#8221;yes&#8221; right_padding_desktop=&#8221;20&#8243; text_align=&#8221;left&#8221; row_position=&#8221;default&#8221; row_position_tablet=&#8221;inherit&#8221; row_position_phone=&#8221;inherit&#8221; overflow=&#8221;visible&#8221; pointer_events=&#8221;all&#8221;][vc_column_inner column_padding=&#8221;padding-5-percent&#8221; column_padding_tablet=&#8221;inherit&#8221; column_padding_phone=&#8221;inherit&#8221; column_padding_position=&#8221;all&#8221; flex_gap_desktop=&#8221;10px&#8221; column_element_direction_desktop=&#8221;default&#8221; column_element_spacing=&#8221;default&#8221; centered_text=&#8221;true&#8221; desktop_text_alignment=&#8221;default&#8221; tablet_text_alignment=&#8221;default&#8221; phone_text_alignment=&#8221;default&#8221; background_color_opacity=&#8221;1&#8243; background_hover_color_opacity=&#8221;1&#8243; column_backdrop_filter=&#8221;none&#8221; column_shadow=&#8221;small_depth&#8221; column_border_radius=&#8221;5px&#8221; column_link_target=&#8221;_self&#8221; overflow=&#8221;visible&#8221; boxed=&#